WEBVTT

00:02.430 --> 00:04.295
[ POLICE RADIO CHA'I'I'ER ]

00:06.500 --> 00:07.762
[ SIGHS ]

00:07.800 --> 00:09.062
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

00:10.070 --> 00:11.662
UH...

00:11.710 --> 00:13.632
YOU LOOK LIKE SOMETHING
THE CAT DUG UP.

00:13.680 --> 00:16.774
I'M PRETTY SURE IT'S "LIKE
SOMETHING THE CAT DRAGGED IN."

00:16.810 --> 00:18.346
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

00:18.380 --> 00:20.746
OH, IT'S NIGHT SHIFTS,
MAN.

00:20.780 --> 00:23.419
MESSES WITH
MY CIRCADIAN RHYTHM.

00:23.450 --> 00:24.348
CIRCADIAN RHYTHM?

00:24.390 --> 00:26.358
SOUNDS LIKE YOU'VE BEEN
IN A WAITING ROOM

00:26.390 --> 00:27.288
READING MAGAZINES.

00:27.320 --> 00:29.129
DOESN'T MAKE IT LESS TRUE.

00:29.160 --> 00:31.355
I MEAN, STAYING UP LATE
MESSES WITH MY SLEEP CYCLE.

00:31.390 --> 00:32.493
CYCLE?

00:32.530 --> 00:34.748
YOU REALIZE YOU'RE SAYING
THESE WORDS OUT LOUD, RIGHT?

00:34.800 --> 00:36.620
[ POLICE RADIO CHA'I'I'ER ]

00:36.670 --> 00:37.568
[ SIGHS ]

00:37.600 --> 00:40.239
DO YOU EVER WISH
YOU WERE NORMAL, YOU KNOW,

00:40.270 --> 00:44.536
LIKE A BANKER
OR SOMETHING, 9:00 TO 5:00,

00:44.570 --> 00:47.573
LIKE ACTUALLY HAD TIME
FOR A REAL LIFE?

00:47.610 --> 00:50.101
I GOT A REAL LIFE.
I GOT A GREAT LIFE.

00:50.150 --> 00:52.516
HOW MANY GUYS GET TO DRIVE
AROUND ALL DAY

00:52.550 --> 00:54.848
LISTENING TO THEIR PARTNERS
TALK ABOUT HIS CYCLES?

00:54.880 --> 00:57.087
DISPATCHER: 1504, uh,
we got a report

00:57.120 --> 00:58.519
of a disturbance in your area.

00:58.550 --> 01:00.814
The Omega Alpha Kappa fraternity
on Admiral Road.

01:00.860 --> 01:03.454
UH, 1504 RESPONDING.

01:04.860 --> 01:06.589
YOU WANT ME TO HIT THEM?
GET THEM.

01:06.630 --> 01:07.619
[ SIREN WAILING ]

01:09.830 --> 01:11.127
[ LOUD ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ]

01:11.170 --> 01:13.138
HEY, BACK THERE.
KILL THE MUSIC!

01:13.170 --> 01:14.432
HEY, THAT'S ENOUGH!

01:14.470 --> 01:15.630
Man: ...DREAMS!

01:15.670 --> 01:16.637
[ GRUNTING INDISTINCTLY ]

01:16.670 --> 01:19.332
HEY! GUYS! STAND UP!

01:19.380 --> 01:20.631
DON'T MAKE ME
TAZE YOUR ASSES.

01:20.680 --> 01:22.409
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]
WHAT'S GOING ON?

01:22.450 --> 01:24.202
HE WAS HITTING
ON MY SISTER.

01:24.250 --> 01:25.376
SOUNDS LIKE A VIOLATION
TO ME.

01:25.410 --> 01:27.173
[ GRUNTS ]

01:27.220 --> 01:28.847
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

01:28.880 --> 01:30.347
HEY. HEY!

01:36.830 --> 01:38.183
HEY.
NO.

01:38.230 --> 01:39.549
WHAT THE HELL?!

01:39.600 --> 01:41.818
[ HANDCUFFS CLICK ]

01:43.730 --> 01:45.368
YOU SHOULD HAVE LET THEM
KNOCK THEMSELVES OUT.

01:45.400 --> 01:47.539
I HAVE THE SITUATION
UNDER CONTROL.

01:49.340 --> 01:50.830
REALLY?

01:54.940 --> 01:58.376
***

01:58.410 --> 01:59.911
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

01:59.950 --> 02:02.248
WE GET THERE,
THESE TWO IDIOTS ARE WASTED,

02:02.290 --> 02:03.143
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN,

02:03.190 --> 02:05.181
CHRIS JUST STARTS WHALING
ON THIS GUY.

02:05.220 --> 02:06.482
WHAT IS HIS PROBLEM?

02:06.520 --> 02:08.181
I DON'T KNOW.
HE JUST WENT OFF.

02:08.220 --> 02:09.357
[ SIGHS ]
SERIOUSLY?

02:09.390 --> 02:10.789
HE DID THAT
AT FITE NITE, TOO.

02:10.830 --> 02:11.683
[ SIREN WAILING ]

02:11.730 --> 02:12.890
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

02:12.930 --> 02:14.522
WELL, HE, I MEAN,
HE JUST WENT NUTS

02:14.560 --> 02:16.391
ON THIS DELIVERY GUY
OVER THE KOSHER WINE.

02:16.430 --> 02:17.294
AND YOU DIDN'T TELL ME?

02:17.330 --> 02:18.922
WELL, I THOUGHT
IT WAS A ONE-TIME THING,

02:18.970 --> 02:20.437
BUT NOW I'M SENSING
IT'S A PATTERN.

02:20.470 --> 02:22.404
HAS HE SAID ANYTHING?
ABOUT WHAT?

02:22.440 --> 02:24.738
UH, ABOUT THIS, ABOUT
WHAT'S HAPPENING WITH HIM.

02:24.770 --> 02:27.830
NO, JUST THAT HIS CIRCADIAN
RHYTHMS ARE OFF.

02:27.880 --> 02:29.802
MAYBE YOU SHOULD TALK
TO HIM.

02:32.820 --> 02:34.879
Jamie: LISTEN, MIDTOWN,
YOU MIGHT WANT TO THINK ABOUT

02:34.920 --> 02:35.818
TAKING A NIGHT OFF.

02:35.850 --> 02:39.354
I TOLD YOU, I'M NOT PARTYING,
I'M WORKING.

02:39.390 --> 02:41.312
OKAY, BUT, UM, YOU'RE STARTING
TO GET THAT LOOK.

02:41.360 --> 02:43.624
[ SCOFFS ]

02:43.660 --> 02:44.627
WHAT LOOK?

02:44.660 --> 02:46.355
THAT "BEST CUSTOMER" LOOK.

02:46.400 --> 02:48.755
IT'S KIND OF LIKE
A TWITCHY PORN STAR

02:48.800 --> 02:50.495
WHO JUST RAN A MARATHON.
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:53.300 --> 02:54.528
LOOK, I CAN GET YOU
THE REST LATER.

02:54.570 --> 02:55.434
[ SIGHS ]

02:55.470 --> 02:57.358
I'M A PATIENT MAN, CHRIS,

02:57.410 --> 02:59.435
BUT, UH, HERE I AM
EXTENDING YOUR CREDIT

02:59.480 --> 03:01.937
AND [CLICKS TONGUE] I DON'T
KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT YOU.

03:01.980 --> 03:04.699
C-COME ON, MAN.
WE'VE -- WE'VE PARTIED.

03:04.750 --> 03:06.547
ALL RIGHT, LOOK.
UH, FRIDAY.
YEAH.

03:06.580 --> 03:07.569
I CAN GET YOU THE REST
BY FRIDAY.

03:07.620 --> 03:08.541
I GET PAID FRIDAY.

03:08.580 --> 03:10.616
[ TAPPING FINGERS ]
TONIGHT.

03:10.650 --> 03:11.480
NO?

03:11.520 --> 03:13.249
NO, MAN. I TOLD YOU,
I GOT TO WORK, OKAY?

03:13.290 --> 03:15.212
I GOT A PLASTER AND PAINT JOB.
IT'S GOT TO BE DONE.

03:15.260 --> 03:17.387
I HATE TO THINK
THAT MY VIRTUE

03:17.430 --> 03:19.990
IS CONTRIBUTING
TO YOUR VICE. [ SIGHS ]

03:20.030 --> 03:22.328
DON'T LET ME THINK THAT,
CHRIS,

03:22.370 --> 03:24.793
'CAUSE I TEND TO ACT OUT
WHEN I FEEL BAD ABOUT MYSELF.

03:26.400 --> 03:28.960
[ TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS
IN DISTANCE ]

03:29.000 --> 03:32.231
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

03:32.280 --> 03:34.430
Oliver: LAST NIGHT,
OFFICERS EPSTEIN AND DIAZ

03:34.480 --> 03:35.378
RESPONDED TO A FIGHT

03:35.410 --> 03:36.547
BETWEEN TWO DRUNKEN
FRATERNITY BROTHERS.

03:36.580 --> 03:39.413
I KNOW, WE ALL KNOW THAT
THERE'S NOTHING MORE DANGEROUS

03:39.450 --> 03:40.678
THAN A COUPLE
OF PREPPY FRAT BOYS

03:40.720 --> 03:43.382
WHO DECIDE TO TAKE OFF THEIR
SCHOOL TIES AND SCUFFLE, RIGHT?

03:43.420 --> 03:45.581
ESPECIALLY WHEN ONE OF THEM
HAS A GUN.
YES, EXACTLY.

03:45.620 --> 03:48.680
IT SEEMS THAT SOME OF OUR,
UH, STUDENTS OF HIGHER LEARNING

03:48.720 --> 03:50.654
HAVE TAKEN TO PACKING
UNREGISTERED FIREARMS.

03:50.690 --> 03:53.693
THERE ARE NO LICENSES, ALL THE
SERIAL NUMBERS ARE FILED OFF,

03:53.730 --> 03:57.359
BUT AS SOON AS OUR LITTLE
HIPSTER IN CELLS GOT SOBER,

03:57.400 --> 03:59.539
HE VERY QUICKLY TOLD US
WHERE HE GOT THIS GUN.

03:59.570 --> 04:00.491
IT'S A BAR ON TECUMSETH.

04:00.540 --> 04:02.428
YOU ARE GOING IN THERE TONIGHT
UNDERCOVER.

04:02.470 --> 04:03.835
BEATS A COLD NIGHT
ON FOOT PATROL.

04:03.870 --> 04:05.838
DETECTIVE PECK
WILL HANDLE THE OPERATION.

04:05.870 --> 04:06.905
YOU'RE GONNA GO IN THERE,

04:06.940 --> 04:08.999
YOU'RE GONNA FIGURE OUT
WHO'S SELLING THESE GUNS,

04:09.040 --> 04:11.349
AND WE'RE GOING TO SHUT
THIS PLACE DOWN FOR GOOD, OKAY?

04:11.380 --> 04:13.974
CHECK THE BOARD TO SEE IF YOU'RE
GOING UNDER, GO GET CHANGED.

04:14.020 --> 04:16.045
THAT'S IT.
EXCEPT FOR YOU, OTHER PECK.

04:16.080 --> 04:18.446
I'M STILL WAITING ON THE JAMESON
MURDER FILE, OKAY?

04:18.490 --> 04:19.957
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

04:19.990 --> 04:20.957
HEY, YOU WANT ME ON THE TEAM,
DON'T YOU?

04:20.990 --> 04:22.287
YEAH, YEAH.
I KNOW.

04:23.330 --> 04:26.788
EYE CANDY OR "HELLO,
I'M CANDY"?

04:28.100 --> 04:29.863
OKAY.

04:34.340 --> 04:35.693
[ GROANS ]
WHAT'S HE DOING HERE?

04:35.740 --> 04:37.833
Nick: I DON'T KNOW.

04:37.870 --> 04:39.371
HEY, DUNCAN
ISN'T YOUR FAILURE.

04:39.410 --> 04:40.809
YOU KNOW THAT, RIGHT?
I KNOW.

04:40.840 --> 04:41.807
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:41.840 --> 04:43.569
YOU SAY YOU KNOW,
BUT YOU DON'T BELIEVE IT.

04:43.610 --> 04:44.645
SOMEWHERE IN MCNALLY-LAND,

04:44.680 --> 04:46.341
THERE'S A STONE TABLET
THAT SAYS IT'S YOUR FAULT.

04:46.380 --> 04:48.416
[ SCOFFS ]
IT'S NOT ON A STONE TABLET.

04:48.450 --> 04:50.987
I MEAN, IT MAY OR MAY NOT BE
STENCILED ON A T-SHIRT, BUT...

04:51.020 --> 04:53.488
LOOK, YOU REPORTED HIM
JUST LIKE WE ALL WOULD HAVE.

04:53.520 --> 04:56.011
[ SIGHS ]

04:58.760 --> 04:59.727
I'M GONNA GO TALK TO HIM.

04:59.760 --> 05:01.091
NO. NO, MCNALLY!
WHAT?!

05:01.130 --> 05:03.963
JUST LEAVE IT.
WALK AWAY.

05:04.000 --> 05:06.389
MCNALLY, COME HERE.

05:06.440 --> 05:07.429
[ DOOR BUZZES ]

05:07.470 --> 05:10.007
THAN KS.

05:10.040 --> 05:11.667
YOU'RE NOT GONNA WORK
THAT OPERATION TONIGHT, OKAY?

05:11.710 --> 05:13.769
WHY? STEVE PECK
JUST BEGGED ME TO.

05:13.810 --> 05:17.075
YEAH, OKAY. ANDY,
YOUR ROOKIE AND HIS LAWYER

05:17.110 --> 05:18.475
JUST MADE
SERIOUS ALLEGATIONS

05:18.510 --> 05:19.943
AGAINST THIS DIVISION
AND AGAINST YOU.

05:19.980 --> 05:21.516
ME PERSONALLY?
YEAH.

05:21.550 --> 05:22.312
ON WHAT GROUNDS?

05:22.350 --> 05:24.409
I MEAN,
I DID EVERYTHING I COULD.

05:24.450 --> 05:25.587
I KNOW. I KNOW THAT.

05:25.620 --> 05:28.088
I KNOW THAT, BUT THIS KID,
HE'S NOT -- NOT GOING QUIETLY.

05:28.120 --> 05:29.951
I MEAN,
THIS IS GONNA BLOW OVER.

05:29.990 --> 05:32.652
LISTEN, I PROMISE.
ANYWAY, HE HAS NO CASE.

05:32.700 --> 05:33.928
YOU HAVEN'T SPOKEN TO HIM,
RIGHT?

05:33.960 --> 05:35.427
SO, YOU HAVEN'T IMPLICATED
YOURSELF.

05:35.460 --> 05:36.825
HEY, IT'S GONNA BE FINE,
BUT UNTIL THEN,

05:36.870 --> 05:38.758
YOU JUST GOT TO MAKE SURE
THAT YOU JUST DOT YOUR 'I's.

05:38.800 --> 05:39.539
PROFESSIONAL STANDARDS

05:39.570 --> 05:40.969
IS GONNA WANT
TO INTERVIEW YOU,

05:41.000 --> 05:42.638
AND THE LAWYERS,
THEY'RE GONNA SUBPOENA

05:42.670 --> 05:44.001
EVERY REPORT
YOU'VE WRITTEN ON HIM.

05:44.040 --> 05:45.166
HE'S STILL
ON THE PAYROLL.

05:45.210 --> 05:48.008
HE'LL BE HERE EVERY MORNING
AT 9:00 AM. CHECKING IN.

05:48.040 --> 05:49.974
HEY, IF YOU SEE HIM,
YOU JUST GO THE OTHER WAY.

05:50.010 --> 05:52.615
NO CONTACT UNTIL
THIS PROCESS PLAYS OUT.

05:52.650 --> 05:54.743
COOL?
YEP.

05:54.780 --> 05:56.589
OKAY, GOOD.

05:56.620 --> 05:57.644
ANGELO PASETTI.

05:57.690 --> 06:01.410
LOCAL BARTENDER, A COUPLE
OF PRIORS -- SMALL-TIME.

06:01.460 --> 06:02.529
HE'S OUR GUN SELLER?

06:02.560 --> 06:03.686
DEFINITELY PART OF IT.

06:03.730 --> 06:04.628
ACCORDING TO FRAT BOY,

06:04.660 --> 06:06.127
THIS SELLER USES ANGELO
TO STAY INSULATED.

06:06.160 --> 06:08.048
YOU FLASH SOME CASH,

06:08.100 --> 06:10.421
ASK ANGELO
FOR A BOBSLED MARTINI.

06:10.470 --> 06:11.960
THAT'S THE CODE WORD,
WHICH, IF HE BITES,

06:12.000 --> 06:13.968
SHOULD GET YOU CLOSER
TO THE GUY SELLING THE GUNS.

06:14.000 --> 06:16.560
YEAH, AND, DIAZ, YOU'RE ON POINT
TO MAKE THE BUY.

06:16.610 --> 06:18.566
DOV, YOU'RE IN FOR COVER.

06:18.610 --> 06:20.578
NICK,
YOU'RE EYES AT THE BAR.

06:20.610 --> 06:22.100
WE'RE GONNA COORDINATE
FROM HERE.
YEAH.

06:22.140 --> 06:23.744
THOSE BILLS,
THEY'RE U.V. PRINTED,

06:23.780 --> 06:24.769
RECORDED SERIAL NUMBERS.

06:24.810 --> 06:25.708
UH, THESE ARE BURNERS.

06:25.750 --> 06:27.809
WE'LL BE LISTENING
ON THE SERVICE CHANNEL.

06:27.850 --> 06:29.886
AS LONG AS YOUR PHONES ARE ON,
WE CAN HEAR YOU,

06:29.920 --> 06:30.989
BUT IT ONLY GOES ONE WAY.

06:31.020 --> 06:32.885
[ DOOR BUZZES ]

06:32.920 --> 06:36.549
[ SAM SIGHS ]

06:36.590 --> 06:39.024
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

06:39.060 --> 06:40.095
HEY. [ SIGHS ]

06:42.030 --> 06:43.895
DID YOU HEAR
ABOUT THE DUNCAN THING?

06:43.930 --> 06:44.828
YEAH.
MM-HMM.

06:44.870 --> 06:46.019
HOW ARE YOU HOLDING UP?

06:46.070 --> 06:47.037
OH, YOU KNOW,
I'M DOING REALLY GREAT.

06:48.800 --> 06:50.961
YEAH, RIGHT.
WHAT ARE YOU WORKING ON?

06:51.010 --> 06:54.434
A MISSING PERSON MAYBE.
NOT SURE YET.

06:54.480 --> 06:57.745
UH, IF YOU'RE FREE,
I COULD USE YOUR HELP.

06:57.780 --> 07:00.647
OH, IS THIS THE WORKPLACE
EQUIVALENT OF PITY SEX?

07:00.680 --> 07:01.817
YEAH, PRETTY MUCH.

07:01.850 --> 07:03.010
I'LL TAKE IT.

07:05.090 --> 07:06.717
MEET BRIAN GOWDY.

07:06.760 --> 07:08.716
HIS BROTHER
REPORTED HIM MISSING,

07:08.760 --> 07:10.682
SAYS HE HASN'T SEEN HIM
IN THREE DAYS,

07:10.730 --> 07:12.721
BROUGHT IN A BUNCH OF STUFF
FROM HIS HOUSE --

07:12.760 --> 07:15.957
BANK STATEMENTS,
MAIL, CELLPHONE.

07:16.000 --> 07:17.820
PASSWORIR/l lP/IROTECT ED.

07:17.870 --> 07:20.191
SO, WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT HIM?

07:20.240 --> 07:24.529
HE'S 32 YEARS OLD, SINGLE,
TEACHER AT LOWERY COLLEGIATE.

07:24.570 --> 07:26.128
WELL, NOT EVERYBODY'S
CUT OUT TO TEACH.

07:26.170 --> 07:29.571
WELL, HE'S REPORTEDLY LOVED
BY HIS STUDENTS.

07:29.610 --> 07:31.771
YEAH, WELL, HE DIDN'T
HAVE DUNCAN, DID HE?

07:31.810 --> 07:32.879
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

07:35.620 --> 07:36.848
I'M GONNA TAKE THIS TO TECH,
SEE IF THEY CAN CRACK THE CODE,

07:36.890 --> 07:38.642
SEE WHO
HE'S BEEN TALKING TO.

07:38.690 --> 07:39.918
SOUNDS GOOD.

07:39.960 --> 07:43.748
CHRIS: Nash, let me know if you
can hear me. Send me a text.

07:43.790 --> 07:45.553
WE'RE UP.
MM-HMM.

07:45.590 --> 07:46.852
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

07:46.900 --> 07:48.891
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES, BEEPS ]
GOOD TO GO.

07:56.740 --> 08:00.801
[ LOUD MUSIC PLAYING ]

08:00.840 --> 08:02.137
SOUNDS LIKE
EVERYONE'S INSIDE.

08:03.250 --> 08:04.706
[ SIGHS ]
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

08:07.320 --> 08:09.618
YOU WISH, UH,
YOU WERE IN THERE?

08:09.650 --> 08:11.083
WHY?

08:11.120 --> 08:13.111
I DON'T KNOW.
YOU LOVE GOING UNDER.

08:13.160 --> 08:16.857
WHAT I LOVE IS SITTING HERE
DRINKING COLD COFFEE WITH YOU.

08:16.890 --> 08:18.858
OH.

08:18.890 --> 08:20.528
WELL [INHALES SHARPLY]
IT'S HOT.

08:20.560 --> 08:23.563
IT'S, UH --
IT'S VERY, VERY HOT.

08:23.600 --> 08:26.228
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:26.270 --> 08:29.603
[ LOUD MUSIC PLAYING ]

08:29.640 --> 08:32.768
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

08:36.680 --> 08:38.545
HEY, UH, VODKA ROCKS?

08:52.930 --> 08:54.522
Suspect spotted
with a case of beer.

08:57.630 --> 08:59.860
NICK SAYS
THAT'S OUR GUY ANGELO.

08:59.900 --> 09:00.639
GOT HIM.

09:00.670 --> 09:01.637
YOU READY?

09:06.210 --> 09:08.235
CHRIS IS AT BAT.

09:08.280 --> 09:10.805
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

09:13.720 --> 09:14.948
CAN I HELP YOU?

09:14.980 --> 09:17.778
I'M LOOKING
FOR A BOBSLED MARTINI.

09:17.820 --> 09:19.913
DON'T KNOW IT.

09:19.960 --> 09:23.123
BEEN LOOKING
ALL OVER FOR IT.

09:23.160 --> 09:24.286
I HEARD
THIS WAS THE PLACE.

09:26.390 --> 09:30.622
A FRIEND OF MINE TOLD ME
ANGELO WAS THE GUY.

09:43.310 --> 09:45.744
HAND IT OVER, OR GET OUT.

09:56.090 --> 09:57.626
HE JUST LOST
THE BANKROLL.

10:07.670 --> 10:08.830
No. Wait.

10:08.870 --> 10:10.804
HE'S COMING BACK.

10:16.240 --> 10:18.174
SO, YOU WANT A BOBSLED,
HUH?

10:21.850 --> 10:24.614
OKAY.
GIVE ME YOUR NUMBER.

10:27.990 --> 10:29.014
IN THE MEANTIME...

10:32.330 --> 10:34.059
...DRINK AND WAIT, HOMBRE.

10:38.230 --> 10:39.766
[ SIGHS ]

10:39.800 --> 10:41.665
[ OPENS BEER BOTTLE ]

10:47.740 --> 10:48.900
[ SIGHS ] OH, MY GOD.

10:50.280 --> 10:51.679
WHAT HAPPENED OVER THERE?

10:51.710 --> 10:54.713
RELAX.
IT'S GONNA BE GREAT.

10:59.790 --> 11:02.759
SO, YOU'VE GOT A STORY.

11:02.790 --> 11:04.155
YEAH, WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

11:04.190 --> 11:06.158
CUTE GUY LIKE YOU
HERE ALONE?

11:06.190 --> 11:07.953
SOMEBODY BROKE YOUR HEART.

11:08.000 --> 11:09.297
SHE LIKES HIM.

11:09.330 --> 11:11.218
NICK:
Maybe I broke hers.

11:11.270 --> 11:13.329
I DON'T THINK
YOU'RE A PLAYER.

11:13.370 --> 11:15.292
NO, I'M NOT,
BUT THANK YOU.

11:15.340 --> 11:16.932
[ CHUCKLES ] FOR WHAT?

11:16.970 --> 11:18.369
FOR SWITCHING STATIONS.

11:18.410 --> 11:21.038
YOU WERE SERVING DOWN THERE,
AND NOW YOU'RE OVER HERE.

11:21.080 --> 11:21.830
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:21.880 --> 11:23.370
MAYBE I LIKE
A CHANGE OF SCENERY.

11:23.410 --> 11:24.445
YEAH.

11:24.480 --> 11:26.448
So, what's your name?

11:26.480 --> 11:27.447
Essie.

11:27.480 --> 11:29.710
Essie? Essie.

11:29.750 --> 11:30.739
OH, DON'T TELL ME.

11:30.790 --> 11:33.156
YOU'RE NAMED AFTER YOUR
GRANDMOTHER -- ESTHER.

11:33.190 --> 11:34.350
NICE.

11:34.390 --> 11:35.982
GUY'S GOT GAME.

11:36.020 --> 11:37.180
REALLY?
MM-HMM.

11:37.230 --> 11:39.027
Y-YOU THINK
WE FALL FOR THAT?

11:39.060 --> 11:40.891
HE'S GONNA ASK HER
WHERE SHE'S FROM NEXT.

11:40.930 --> 11:41.794
NO, COME ON.

11:41.830 --> 11:42.865
NICK: So, where are you from,
Esther?

11:42.900 --> 11:46.290
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO WORK
A LITTLE HARDER THAN THAT.

11:48.840 --> 11:52.162
SO, BRIAN GOWDY CANCELED
HIS CREDIT CARD TWO WEEKS AGO,

11:52.210 --> 11:55.031
SOLD HIS CONDO,
AND HIS LAST ATM WITHDRAWAL

11:55.080 --> 11:56.900
WAS AT A GAS STATION
THREE DAYS AGO.

11:56.950 --> 11:58.201
[ SIGHS ]

11:58.250 --> 12:01.469
SO, HE'S WITHDRAWING
HIS MAXIMUM DAILY LIMIT

12:01.520 --> 12:03.841
FOR, LIKE,
THE LAST THREE WEEKS?

12:03.890 --> 12:04.709
MM-HMM.

12:04.750 --> 12:06.115
WELL, NO WONDER
HE'S OFF THE RADAR.

12:06.150 --> 12:07.219
HE'S, UH,
HE'S JUST USING CASH.

12:07.260 --> 12:08.909
WELL,
HE'S A GROWN-UP RUNAWAY...

12:08.960 --> 12:11.178
[ SIGHS ]
...WHICH SOUNDS AWESOME,
YOU KNOW?

12:11.230 --> 12:13.255
GET AWAY FROM YOUR TROUBLES
AND YOUR DEBTS

12:13.300 --> 12:15.029
AND YOUR...EVERYTHING.

12:15.060 --> 12:17.164
YOU WANT TO TALK ABOUT IT,
MCNALLY?

12:17.200 --> 12:19.020
NO, THERE'S NOTHING
TO TALK ABOUT. [ SIGHS ]

12:19.070 --> 12:20.435
LOOK, LET'S JUST
KEEP DIGGING, OKAY?

12:20.470 --> 12:21.789
YOU STICK WITH
THE CREDIT-CARD STATEMENTS,

12:21.840 --> 12:22.534
AND I'LL DO
THE BANK ACCOUNTS.

12:22.570 --> 12:24.367
THANK YOU.
OKAY.

12:27.910 --> 12:30.071
[ KEYS CLACKING ]

12:30.110 --> 12:31.873
[ WHISTLING ]

12:31.910 --> 12:33.775
HEY, OL--OLIVER'S
LOOKING FOR YOU.

12:33.820 --> 12:34.809
[ Strained ]
CAN YOU HELP ME, PLEASE?

12:34.850 --> 12:35.839
YES. UM...

12:37.350 --> 12:38.783
OH, IT'S STUCK
IN YOUR HAIR.

12:38.820 --> 12:39.787
OKAY, ARMS UP.

12:39.820 --> 12:41.515
ARMS UP.
NARROW YOUR SHOULDERS.

12:41.560 --> 12:42.982
OKAY, I TOTALLY GET
WHAT'S HAPPENING.

12:43.030 --> 12:44.327
THIS HAPPENS
WHEN I PUT ON A TURTLENECK.

12:44.360 --> 12:45.520
IT FEELS LIKE
I'M BEING STRANGLED.

12:45.560 --> 12:46.925
[ GRUNTS ]

12:46.960 --> 12:49.190
OKAY.
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

12:49.230 --> 12:50.925
HERE YOU GO.

12:50.970 --> 12:52.460
I WANT YOU TO KEEP IT.

12:52.500 --> 12:54.092
YOU'RE A TINY,
LITTLE CREATURE.

12:57.040 --> 12:58.200
[ WATER RUNS ]

13:01.340 --> 13:02.375
OY. ARE YOU OKAY?

13:02.410 --> 13:06.301
UH, 'CAUSE YOU KEEP, YOU KNOW,
BUYING ALL THIS CRAP

13:06.350 --> 13:08.341
AND THEN
JUST GIVING IT AWAY.

13:08.380 --> 13:10.484
THIS IS STAFF SERGEANT SHAW.

13:10.520 --> 13:13.114
UH, PUT YOUR CLOTHES ON.
I'M COMING IN THERE AFTER PECK.

13:15.090 --> 13:17.888
JAMESON MURDERS.
WHERE'S YOUR REPORT?

13:17.930 --> 13:20.899
UH, YEAH, I'M --
I'M WORKING ON IT, OLIVER.

13:20.930 --> 13:22.192
YOU KEEP SAYING THAT.

13:22.230 --> 13:23.390
'CAUSE IT'S TRUE.

13:24.930 --> 13:26.898
I GOT THIS FOR YOU.

13:26.940 --> 13:28.567
A WOMAN
WAS SHOT AND KILLED.

13:28.600 --> 13:31.160
I KNOW.
SHE LEFT
A LITTLE GIRL BEHIND.

13:31.210 --> 13:32.268
I KNOW.

13:32.310 --> 13:35.108
I CANNOT CLOSE THAT CASE
WITHOUT YOUR WITNESS REPORTS.

13:35.140 --> 13:36.437
I KNOW.

13:36.480 --> 13:38.243
YEAH.
[ SNIFFS ]

13:38.280 --> 13:39.975
YOU HAVE AN HOUR.

13:46.120 --> 13:47.485
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

13:47.520 --> 13:49.056
[ LOUD MUSIC PLAYING ]

13:53.130 --> 13:56.099
[ CELLPHONE KEYS CLACKING ]

13:56.130 --> 13:58.064
LOOK AT US.

13:58.100 --> 14:00.466
A BAR FULL OF PEOPLE AND HERE
WE ARE GLUED TO OUR PHONES.

14:00.500 --> 14:02.138
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:02.170 --> 14:06.937
IT'S MY STUPID EX.
HE WON'T LEAVE ME ALONE.

14:06.980 --> 14:07.969
YEAH, WELL, SOMEONE
SHOULD TELL HIM

14:08.010 --> 14:09.432
THAT CONSTANT TEXTING
ISN'T HELPING HIS CASE.

14:09.480 --> 14:10.469
ESSIE: [ Chuckles ]
SEE?

14:10.510 --> 14:13.070
Looking like Ryan Gosling
wouldn't help this guy.

14:13.120 --> 14:14.246
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

14:14.280 --> 14:16.419
UH, SURPRISE ME.
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:16.450 --> 14:18.384
YOU SURE YOU TRUST ME?

14:18.420 --> 14:20.980
OH, YEAH.
I'M OPEN FOR ANYTHING.

14:22.260 --> 14:25.081
[ Chuckling ] "OPEN TO
ANYTHING"? COME ON, NICK.

14:25.130 --> 14:26.654
WHAT?
THAT'S NOT A BAD LINE.

14:26.690 --> 14:29.488
PSHH!
NICK: Essie, I am placing
myself in your capable hands.

14:29.530 --> 14:31.191
OKAY, THAT MIGHT BE
PUSHING IT.

14:31.230 --> 14:32.265
RIGHT?

14:33.340 --> 14:34.238
CHECK IT OUT.

14:34.270 --> 14:36.397
GUY BY THE SPEAKER
LOOKS LIKE HE'S DEALING.

14:42.010 --> 14:45.047
LOOKS LIKE HE'S DOING
A BOOMING BUSINESS.

14:45.080 --> 14:46.570
FORGET HIM.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

14:46.610 --> 14:48.271
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES, BEEPS ]

14:48.320 --> 14:50.140
HE'S NOT OUR PROBLEM
TONIGHT.

14:50.190 --> 14:51.316
UNKNOWN NUMBER.

14:51.350 --> 14:53.318
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES, BEEPS ]

14:53.360 --> 14:55.612
"DROP $500 IN THE
BATHROOM TOWEL DISPENSER."

15:15.310 --> 15:16.470
MADE THE DROP.

15:16.510 --> 15:19.206
FRAT BOY SAID THAT HE DROPPED
THE MONEY IN THE COAT ROOM.

15:19.250 --> 15:20.319
WHY CHANGE PLANS?

15:20.350 --> 15:21.374
WHY NOT CHANGE PLANS?

15:21.420 --> 15:24.617
SHAKE UP THEIR ROUTINE --
IT'S GOOD SECURITY, RIGHT?

15:24.650 --> 15:25.947
YEAH.

15:30.190 --> 15:32.454
Jamie: MIDTOWN,
WHERE'D YOU GO, MAN?

15:39.000 --> 15:41.264
WHAT HAPPENED?
WE LOST SOUND.

15:41.300 --> 15:42.961
ALL RIGHT. TEXT DOV,
GET HIM IN THERE.

15:43.010 --> 15:44.068
[ KEYS CLACKING ]

15:52.250 --> 15:54.115
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:54.150 --> 15:55.344
OKAY, LISTEN.

15:55.380 --> 15:57.189
YOU'RE HIDING FROM ME?
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

15:57.220 --> 15:58.039
THAT'S SO CUTE, YO.

15:58.090 --> 15:59.114
NO, I'M --

15:59.150 --> 16:01.084
NOW, YOU KNOW, THE THING IS,
I SAW YOU UPSTAIRS.

16:01.120 --> 16:03.350
I'M PRETTY SURE
I SAW COPS OUT THERE.

16:03.390 --> 16:04.482
NO, I THOUGHT
YOU WERE WORKING.

16:04.530 --> 16:07.192
YEAH, I -- I DID THAT,
AND NOW --

16:07.230 --> 16:09.152
NOW LISTEN, MIDTOWN, OKAY?

16:09.200 --> 16:12.226
YOU DON'T PRODUCE THE KALE,
THEN THE DARKNESS DESCENDS,

16:12.270 --> 16:13.396
AND I'M TALKING ABOUT DANTE.

16:13.440 --> 16:15.169
I'M SERIOUS, DUDE.

16:15.200 --> 16:17.304
MY GUY,
HE'S GOT DENTAL EQUIPMENT.

16:17.340 --> 16:18.034
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:18.070 --> 16:21.176
I'M GONNA PAY YOU, OKAY?
AND I --

16:21.210 --> 16:22.279
HOW ABOUT YOU BRING OUT
YOUR PHONE

16:22.310 --> 16:25.040
AND YOU CALL YOUR FAMILY
OR YOUR FRIENDS, YOUR MOTHER,

16:25.080 --> 16:26.172
YOUR FATHER, YOU KNOW,
WHOEVER,

16:26.210 --> 16:28.212
AND YOU TELL THEM TO BRING ME
VAST SUMS OF MONEY, OKAY?

16:28.250 --> 16:31.117
CAN YOU DO THAT?

16:31.150 --> 16:32.742
I'LL SEE YOU SOON.

16:40.700 --> 16:42.224
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED
TO YOUR PHONE?

16:42.260 --> 16:44.399
OH, I...COULDN'T GET
ANY BARS.

16:46.400 --> 16:48.288
YOU GOT THEM NOW.

16:48.340 --> 16:51.002
YEAH [SIGHS]
CRAZY THINGS.

16:52.810 --> 16:54.232
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

16:54.280 --> 16:57.101
HMM? YEAH.

16:57.150 --> 16:59.141
I'M FINE.

17:04.820 --> 17:06.515
[ LOUD MUSIC PLAYING ]

17:06.550 --> 17:08.051
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

17:15.660 --> 17:16.627
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

17:16.660 --> 17:18.491
IF YOU DON'T CHILL,
YOU'RE GONNA BLOW THIS.

17:18.530 --> 17:19.827
IT'S TAKING TOO LONG.

17:19.870 --> 17:21.497
IT'S NOT A PIZZA DELIVERY.

17:23.610 --> 17:25.168
JUST GIVE ME A BREAK,
OKAY?

17:25.210 --> 17:28.099
IT'S MY FIRST GUN DEAL.

17:28.140 --> 17:29.232
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES, BEEPS ]

17:29.280 --> 17:30.349
HEY. HEY, HEY, HEY.

17:33.550 --> 17:35.438
"BACK ALLEY.
FIVE MIN UTES."

17:35.480 --> 17:37.414
OKAY, I'LL GO OUT FRONT
AND GET IN POSITION.

17:45.890 --> 17:48.620
OKAY.

17:48.660 --> 17:50.719
CHRIS IS IN POSITION.

17:52.570 --> 17:54.788
[ HORN HONKS ]

17:57.570 --> 17:59.834
DOV:
It's the dealer from inside.

17:59.870 --> 18:02.407
MAYBE HE'S BRANCHING OUT.
MAYBE HE'S OUR GUN SELLER.

18:02.440 --> 18:04.647
WHAT IS GOING ON?

18:04.680 --> 18:08.377
DIAZ, MAN, I THOUGHT
I TOLD YOU NOT TO LEAVE.

18:08.420 --> 18:10.240
LOOK, JAMIE, YOU GOT
TO GET OUT OF HERE.

18:10.290 --> 18:11.746
NO.

18:11.790 --> 18:14.418
THERE DOESN'T SEEM TO BE
AN EXCHANGE.

18:14.460 --> 18:17.486
WE LOST CHRIS AGAIN.

18:17.530 --> 18:18.758
MOVING IN.
[ SIREN WAILING ]

18:18.790 --> 18:20.519
JUST GO WITH IT, OKAY?

18:20.560 --> 18:22.118
[ GRUNTS LOUDLY ]
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST

18:22.160 --> 18:23.661
FOR POSSESSION
OF A CONTROLLED SUBSTANCE.

18:23.700 --> 18:24.689
YOU'RE A COP?

18:24.730 --> 18:26.561
DUDE, THIS IS A SERIOUS
BREACH OF ETIQUETTE, MAN!

18:26.600 --> 18:28.397
Is he our guy?

18:28.440 --> 18:29.668
CHRIS: N0.

18:29.700 --> 18:32.533
HE WAS WAVING AROUND THIS
IN PLAIN SIGHT.

18:32.570 --> 18:33.639
WHAT WAS I
SUPPOSED TO DO?

18:33.680 --> 18:34.738
YOU COULD'VE MOVED HIM ON.

18:34.780 --> 18:36.372
YEAH, COME ON, MAN,
I CAN MOVE, MAN.

18:36.410 --> 18:38.275
I CAN MOVE! AAH!
SHUT UP!

18:38.310 --> 18:39.504
STEVE: Epstein, it's Peck.

18:39.550 --> 18:41.347
YEAH, OUR GUN SELLER
DIDN'T SHOW.

18:41.380 --> 18:43.382
CHRIS BUSTED SOME DEALER
FOR POSSESSION.

18:43.420 --> 18:46.139
LISTEN, I CAN GET HIM
OUT OF HERE, OKAY?

18:46.190 --> 18:47.350
WHY DON'T I TAKE HIM
A COUPLE BLOCKS FROM HERE

18:47.390 --> 18:48.812
AND KICK HIM LOOSE?
WE CAN'T LET HIM GO

18:48.860 --> 18:49.884
OR HE'LL BLOW
THIS WHOLE THING.

18:49.920 --> 18:52.150
HE'LL NEED TO BE PROCESSED.
CHRIS CAN TAKE HIM.

18:52.190 --> 18:53.521
Forget it.
He burned you both.

18:53.560 --> 18:55.448
YEAH, ALL RIGHT.
WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

18:55.500 --> 18:56.922
DOV, I CAN HANDLE THIS,
OKAY?

18:56.960 --> 18:58.769
IT'S NOT OUR DECISION.
LET'S GO.

19:00.970 --> 19:02.369
[ GRUNTING ]
COME ON, MAN!

19:09.610 --> 19:11.271
YEAH, I'M IN HERE NOW.

19:11.310 --> 19:13.915
TRACI: Just get the money
and get out.

19:13.950 --> 19:15.577
UH, MONEY'S GONE.

19:15.620 --> 19:16.609
ANGELO MUST HAVE IT.

19:16.650 --> 19:18.208
WE COULD PULL HIM IN NOW,
OR I COULD HANG BACK,

19:18.250 --> 19:19.239
SEE WHO HE CONNECTS WITH.

19:19.290 --> 19:21.758
JUST STAY IN THERE
AND JUST SEE WHAT YOU CAN SEE.

19:21.790 --> 19:22.688
GREAT.

19:22.720 --> 19:25.427
SO, WE'VE LOST OUR FLASH MONEY
AND NO GUN.

19:25.460 --> 19:27.519
IT'S JUST UNBELIEVABLE.
[ SIGHS ]

19:27.560 --> 19:28.629
[ LOUD MUSIC PLAYING ]

19:28.660 --> 19:30.628
HEY, I THOUGHT YOU LEFT.

19:30.670 --> 19:31.762
NO, NOT YET.

19:31.800 --> 19:34.268
GOOD. DON'T.

19:34.300 --> 19:36.393
YOU MUST
BE GETTING TIRED.

19:36.440 --> 19:39.739
NO. I'M USED TO
STAYING UP ALL NIGHT.

19:42.640 --> 19:45.200
HEY, YOU EVER, UM --

19:45.250 --> 19:46.774
YOU EVER WANT TO SAY "SCREW IT"
TO WORK,

19:46.810 --> 19:47.913
JUST DO WHAT YOU WANT?

19:47.950 --> 19:50.680
YOU MEAN LIKE RIGHT NOW?
YEAH.

19:50.720 --> 19:54.281
ESSIE, COME ON.
WE'RE GETTING SLAMMED.

19:54.320 --> 19:55.617
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:03.570 --> 20:05.390
HEY, I'LL, UH,
TAKE CARE OF BOOKING

20:05.430 --> 20:07.534
IF YOU WANT TO GET STARTED
ON THE PAPERWORK.

20:11.440 --> 20:12.930
YO, WHAT THE HELL?
THIS IS CRAZY.

20:12.970 --> 20:14.574
LOOK, YOU THINK
I WANTED TO ARREST --
ARREST ME?

20:14.610 --> 20:15.508
KIND OF WHAT COPS
ARE SUPPOSED TO DO.

20:15.540 --> 20:17.246
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY'RE NOT
SUPPOSED TO DO

20:17.280 --> 20:18.679
IS BUY MY DRUGS,
ALL RIGHT?

20:18.710 --> 20:20.519
YOUR WORLDS
ARE COLLIDING, DIAZ.

20:20.550 --> 20:21.869
LOOK, WE CAN STILL
FIGURE THIS OUT.

20:21.920 --> 20:22.909
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

20:22.950 --> 20:24.611
AIN'T NO HACK FOR THIS.

20:24.650 --> 20:26.618
LOOK...
[ BEEP ]

20:26.650 --> 20:29.813
...YOU'RE BEING PROCESSED,
BUT WE HAVEN'T CHARGED YOU YET.

20:29.860 --> 20:31.828
I CAN STILL
GET YOU OUT OF THIS.

20:31.860 --> 20:33.521
YOU KNOW
WHAT I'M GONNA DO?

20:33.560 --> 20:35.994
I GONNA STAY STEALTH
UNTIL I SEE THE SUN COME UP.

20:36.030 --> 20:38.567
THEN I'M GONNA GO MAKE A DEAL
WITH A PROSECUTOR,

20:38.600 --> 20:40.932
AND THE FIRST NAME
I'M GONNA GIVE UP IS YOURS.

20:43.910 --> 20:46.606
STAND AGAINST THE WALL.

20:46.640 --> 20:47.834
STAY TH ERE.

20:47.880 --> 20:48.938
[ SIGHS ]

20:48.980 --> 20:50.641
SIX MONTHS
OF BANK STATEMENTS.

20:50.680 --> 20:53.319
I MEAN, NONE OF THIS SPENDING
LOOKS LIKE A DRUG ISSUE.

20:53.350 --> 20:54.715
NO 3:00 AM. WITHDRAWALS,

20:54.750 --> 20:57.583
I MEAN, REGULAR SHOPPING HABITS
FOR GROCERIES --

20:57.620 --> 20:59.645
ORGANIC, NO LESS.
YEAH.

20:59.690 --> 21:00.554
SO, HIS BROTHER SAID

21:00.590 --> 21:02.478
HE DIDN'T NOTICE ANY CHANGES
IN HIM, RIGHT?

21:02.520 --> 21:04.784
NO. DIDN'T SEEM STRESSED
OR UNHAPPY.

21:04.830 --> 21:06.855
NO ANTIDEPRESSANT
PRESCRIPTIONS

21:06.890 --> 21:08.926
OR PAYMENTS
TO A PSYCHOLOGIST.

21:08.960 --> 21:10.928
ALL RIGHT.

21:10.970 --> 21:13.791
SO, SELLS HIS CONDO,
HE TAKES OUT ALL THIS MONEY.

21:13.840 --> 21:16.832
I MEAN, MAYBE IT'S POSSIBLE
WE'RE LOOKING AT EXTORTION

21:16.870 --> 21:18.337
OR BLACKMAIL, YOU KNOW?

21:18.370 --> 21:19.564
MAYBE HE'S GOT
A DARK SECRET.

21:19.610 --> 21:20.577
I DOUBT IT.
THIS GUY'S LIFE

21:20.610 --> 21:22.635
READS LIKE THE MOST BORING NOVEL
IN THE WORLD,

21:22.680 --> 21:25.342
EXCEPT FOR THIS.

21:25.380 --> 21:27.314
HE SPENT QUITE A BIT OF MONEY
IN COSTA RICA

21:27.350 --> 21:28.612
OVER THE LAST SIX MONTHS --

21:28.650 --> 21:32.586
HOTEL CHARGES, RESTAURANTS --
AT LEAST THREE DIFFERENT TRIPS.

21:34.620 --> 21:35.484
WHERE WOULD YOU GO

21:35.520 --> 21:36.748
IF YOU HAD TO LEAVE
YOUR LIFE BEHIND?

21:36.790 --> 21:39.759
I WOULDN'T GO ANYWHERE...

21:39.790 --> 21:41.997
UNLESS YOU WERE COMING
WITH ME.

21:42.030 --> 21:43.793
AW.

21:43.830 --> 21:45.923
SO, THE BEACH --
MAI TAIS, HOT SUN,

21:45.970 --> 21:47.790
AND NOT A CARE
IN THE WORLD.

21:47.840 --> 21:49.330
I SAY WE GO NORTH.

21:49.370 --> 21:50.928
NO, THAT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.
I HATE THE COLD.

21:50.970 --> 21:51.959
OH, COME ON.

21:52.010 --> 21:54.535
DOGSLEDDING
UNDER AN ARCTIC MOON,

21:54.580 --> 21:56.832
THOSE CRAZY NORTHERN LIGHTS,
AND NOBODY WOULD EVER FIND US.

21:56.880 --> 21:58.040
PERFECT.

21:58.080 --> 22:00.344
SO, WE'RE BASICALLY NEVER GONNA
AGREE ON A PLACE TO RETIRE,

22:00.380 --> 22:01.677
WHICH MEANS
WE SHOULD JUST BE FRIENDS

22:01.720 --> 22:02.448
FOR THE REST OF OUR LIVES.

22:02.480 --> 22:03.640
HEY, N-NO, NO.
I LOVE THE BEACH.

22:03.690 --> 22:04.918
SAND IN MY SANDWICH -- MMM.

22:04.950 --> 22:06.679
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:06.720 --> 22:10.429
OH.
LOOK AT THIS.

22:11.860 --> 22:13.521
PACIFICO COLLEGE --

22:13.560 --> 22:16.097
"AN INTERNATIONAL SCHOOL
OF ART AND COMPASSION."

22:16.130 --> 22:16.994
FANCY, YEAH?

22:17.030 --> 22:20.534
IN...SAN JOS,
COSTA RICA!

22:20.570 --> 22:23.835
MR. BRIAN GOWDY GOT HIMSELF
A NEW JOB,

22:23.870 --> 22:25.599
AND IT COMES WITH A CONDO.

22:25.640 --> 22:26.334
SO, THAT'S THAT.

22:26.370 --> 22:27.701
WANT ME
TO CALL LOCAL POLICE,

22:27.740 --> 22:28.900
MAKE SURE
HE GOT THERE SAFELY?

22:28.940 --> 22:31.545
UH, I DO SPEAK
FLUENT SPANISH.

22:31.580 --> 22:32.945
YOU KNOW THAT, RIGHT?
[ CHUCKLES ]
OH, I'M AWARE.

22:32.980 --> 22:35.517
I JUST THOUGHT THAT WAS RESERVED
FOR WHEN YOU WERE NAKED.

22:35.550 --> 22:37.711
[ SIGHS ]

22:37.750 --> 22:40.753
WELL, THIS HAS BEEN
A REAL BLAST.

22:40.790 --> 22:42.712
I'M GONNA GO STRESS-EAT
ALL OF GAIL'S RAW FOOD
IN THE FRIDGE.

22:42.760 --> 22:45.058
[ SIGHS ]

22:45.090 --> 22:46.921
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

22:46.960 --> 22:49.554
GAIL PECK!

22:49.600 --> 22:51.465
I KNOW YOU'RE HERE SOMEWHERE.

22:51.500 --> 22:53.161
WHERE THE HELL IS MY REPORT?

22:53.200 --> 22:56.590
MY OFFICE, THREE MINUTES!

23:06.750 --> 23:08.115
I'M SORRY
I DIDN'T KNOCK.

23:08.150 --> 23:10.448
I...DIDN'T REALLY THINK
ABOUT IT TILL NOW,

23:10.490 --> 23:11.445
AND NOW IT'S TOO LATE.

23:11.490 --> 23:12.718
[ DRAWER SLAMS ]
[ GRUNTS ]

23:12.750 --> 23:14.854
UH...
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

23:14.890 --> 23:17.085
[ GRUNTS ]
[ DRAWER SLAMS ]

23:17.120 --> 23:18.087
WHAT'S UP?

23:18.130 --> 23:20.451
UH [STUTTERS] I'M A LITTLE
WORRIED ABOUT GAIL.

23:20.500 --> 23:22.456
DO -- DO YOU NEED HELP?
NOPE.

23:22.500 --> 23:23.489
[ DRAWER SLAMS ]
[ SIGHS ]

23:23.530 --> 23:25.623
IT'S...
[ DRAWER CLOSES ]

23:25.670 --> 23:27.968
SHE SEEMS
A LITTLE MESSED UP.

23:28.000 --> 23:29.968
THAT'S GAIL.
SHE'S ALWAYS MESSED UP.

23:30.000 --> 23:33.800
YEAH, IT'S -- I JUST DON'T WANT
HER SHAVING OFF ALL HER HAIR

23:33.840 --> 23:36.968
AND THEN BUYING ONE OF THOSE
AMANDA BYNES TURQUOISE WIGS.

23:37.010 --> 23:38.568
OKAY, WAIT. WHAT?

23:38.610 --> 23:41.773
TWO THINGS -- HOW DOES --
W-- HOW DOES THIS WORK?

23:41.820 --> 23:43.845
OH, IT'S JUST A LIFT,
SHIFT, CLOSE, SO...

23:46.520 --> 23:47.509
RIGHT. GAIL. OKAY.

23:47.560 --> 23:48.788
I SHOULD --
I'M GONNA GO AND...

23:48.820 --> 23:50.549
USE YOUR WORDS.
TALK TO HER.

23:50.590 --> 23:53.150
WHATEVER YOU THINK, SIR.

23:53.190 --> 23:55.829
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

23:55.860 --> 23:58.920
[ SIGHS ]

23:58.970 --> 24:03.737
SO, DUNCAN FILED A COMPLAINT
AGAINST YOU.

24:03.770 --> 24:05.101
IT HAPPENS...
TO EVERYONE.

24:05.140 --> 24:06.835
NOT TO ME.

24:06.870 --> 24:08.929
YES, TO YOU, TO ME,
TO ALL OF US.

24:08.980 --> 24:10.800
IT'S A COP
RITE OF PASSAGE.

24:10.850 --> 24:12.249
FIRST TIME I WAS SUED,

24:12.280 --> 24:15.215
I GOT A LEGAL-AID LAWYER
WITH A $10 SUIT.

24:15.250 --> 24:18.242
WE SHOW UP FOR MY DEPOSITION
AT AN OLD-LINE LAW FIRM,

24:18.290 --> 24:19.917
A HUNDRED SENIOR PARTNERS,

24:19.950 --> 24:22.589
FULL-TIME CURATOR
FOR THE ART ON THE WALLS.

24:22.620 --> 24:24.588
THE CAMERA
STARTS ROLLING --
STOP IT.

24:24.630 --> 24:26.552
STOP, OKAY?
I'M ALREADY NERVOUS.

24:26.590 --> 24:29.718
...AND I THROW UP
ALL OVER THE MAHOGANY TABLE.

24:29.760 --> 24:32.991
OKAY. THANK YOU
FOR SHARING THAT.

24:33.030 --> 24:35.567
THAT'S A GREAT STORY.
NOVEL, EVEN.

24:35.600 --> 24:36.965
BUT YOU MIGHT WANT
TO RECONSIDER

24:37.000 --> 24:38.228
HOW THAT'S REASSURING
TO ME.

24:38.270 --> 24:39.999
DO YOU KNOW
THAT THERE ARE PEOPLE

24:40.040 --> 24:41.678
WHO TRY
TO SUE WEATHER STATIONS

24:41.710 --> 24:43.132
FOR INACCURATE
WEATHER REPORTS?

24:43.180 --> 24:46.502
THERE WAS A SURFER ONCE
WHO SUED ANOTHER SURFER

24:46.550 --> 24:48.745
FOR STEALING HIS WAVE.
SO WHAT?

24:48.780 --> 24:50.179
SO, JUST BECAUSE
SOMEBODY FILES A COMPLAINT

24:50.220 --> 24:51.585
DOESN'T MEAN
THEY'RE GONNA WIN.

24:51.620 --> 24:53.110
WHAT IF DUNCAN'S RIGHT?

24:53.150 --> 24:55.254
WHAT IF I GAVE UP
TOO SOON?

24:55.290 --> 24:58.123
IF YOUR GUT SAID THAT THAT KID
WASN'T FIT TO HAVE A BADGE,

24:58.160 --> 24:59.855
THEN HE DOES NOT
DESERVE ONE.

24:59.890 --> 25:03.997
I LEFT STUFF OUT
OF THE REPORTS.

25:04.030 --> 25:05.588
WHAT KIND OF STUFF?

25:05.630 --> 25:08.667
TH-THE GUY
IS HOPELESS, OKAY?

25:08.700 --> 25:10.861
SO, I -- I JUST TRIED
TO PUT A POSITIVE SPIN

25:10.910 --> 25:11.808
ON THE THINGS
I WAS PUTTING IN THERE,

25:11.840 --> 25:13.137
AND IN DOING THAT,

25:13.170 --> 25:16.230
I LEFT THINGS OUT
THAT SHOULD BE IN THERE.

25:16.280 --> 25:18.748
I JUST FIGURED HE WOULD GET IT
TOGETHER, YOU KNOW,

25:18.780 --> 25:20.270
WORK IT OUT,
BUT HE'S THE WORST.

25:22.120 --> 25:23.781
[ SIGHS ]

25:23.820 --> 25:26.209
THEY'RE GONNA FIND OUT
I LIED.

25:26.250 --> 25:28.286
THEN WHAT?

25:28.320 --> 25:31.824
WELL, I HEAR CONDOS ARE
REALLY CHEAP IN COSTA RICA.

25:31.860 --> 25:32.679
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:32.730 --> 25:34.095
WE COULD GET ONE
RIGHT ON THE BEACH.

25:41.040 --> 25:42.189
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

25:45.740 --> 25:47.879
LOOK, I'M SORRY.

25:47.910 --> 25:49.935
I DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

25:49.980 --> 25:52.175
NO, I KNOW IT'S MY FAULT
WE GOT PULLED OUT.

25:52.210 --> 25:53.939
I SHOULD HAVE NEVER
ARRESTED THAT GUY.

25:53.980 --> 25:55.049
FORGET IT.

25:57.220 --> 26:00.144
BUT MAYBE WE COULD STILL
TURN THIS THING AROUND.

26:00.190 --> 26:01.157
CHRIS, IT'S DONE.

26:01.190 --> 26:02.748
WAIT A MINUTE. WHAT IF WE PUSH
THIS JAMIE GUY,

26:02.790 --> 26:04.155
USE HIM TO CATCH
A BIGGER FISH?

26:04.190 --> 26:05.657
LEAVE IT
TO THE DRUG SQUAD.

26:05.690 --> 26:06.281
NO.

26:06.330 --> 26:09.094
I'M GONNA DO THIS THING,

26:09.130 --> 26:11.291
AND WHEN IT PANS OUT, I'M
PUTTING YOUR NAME IN LIGHTS.

26:11.330 --> 26:12.888
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:22.280 --> 26:26.102
OH...THERE HE IS.

26:26.150 --> 26:28.618
SEE THAT SUN
COMING UP YET?

26:28.650 --> 26:29.742
SHUT UP AND LISTEN.

26:29.780 --> 26:31.611
THE ONLY WAY I CAN
GET YOU OUT OF THIS --

26:31.650 --> 26:32.912
NO, GET YOU OUT OF THIS.

26:32.950 --> 26:34.679
YOU GOT TO GIVE US
A NAME.

26:34.720 --> 26:35.857
YOU ASKING ME TO BE
A RAT?

26:35.890 --> 26:36.879
CONFIDENTIAL INFORMANT.

26:36.920 --> 26:38.251
OH, YEAH,
THAT SOUNDS BETTER.

26:38.290 --> 26:40.326
THAT'S KIND OF LIKE
A TRUSTED ADVISER?

26:40.360 --> 26:42.396
I'M GONNA GO
WITH, UH, NO.

26:42.430 --> 26:45.126
LISTEN, BEING A C.I.
IS KIND OF LIKE

26:45.170 --> 26:47.297
GETTING A "GET OUT
OF JAIL FREE" CARD --

26:47.330 --> 26:51.164
YOU'RE PROTECTED,
YOU GET TO KEEP SELLING.

26:51.210 --> 26:53.303
ALL YOU GOT TO DO
IS GIVE US THE RIGHT NAME,

26:53.340 --> 26:55.069
YOU WALK OUT OF HERE
A FREE MAN.

26:56.910 --> 26:59.299
THE RIGHT NAME?
YEAH.

26:59.350 --> 27:04.049
I'M GONNA GO
WITH, UM, CHRIS DIAZ.

27:04.090 --> 27:07.184
[ SCOFF
S
HUH? ]

27:07.220 --> 27:09.814
YOU THINK YOU'RE THE FIRST
DEALER TO EVER TRY THAT?

27:09.860 --> 27:12.727
IT'S NOT GONNA WORK.
WON'T WORK.

27:12.760 --> 27:17.220
I'M SORRY, JAMIE, BUT THEY'RE
JUST NOT GONNA BELIEVE YOU.

27:17.260 --> 27:19.091
FIGURED YOU FOR SMARTER.

27:21.040 --> 27:23.804
WHOA, DIAZ, I'M -- CO--

27:25.370 --> 27:28.430
DIAZ, WAIT UP!

27:28.480 --> 27:29.731
DIAZ, C--

27:36.120 --> 27:36.939
Sam: BUENO.

27:36.980 --> 27:38.880
Y YA TIENES MI NUMERO
DE TELEFONO, NO?

27:38.920 --> 27:41.115
LLAMAME SI LLEGA.
OKAY?

27:41.160 --> 27:43.754
S. GRACIAS.

27:43.790 --> 27:46.020
THAT WAS THE MANAGER
OF BRIAN'S CONDO IN COSTA RICA,

27:46.060 --> 27:47.220
AND BRIAN'S NOT THERE.

27:47.260 --> 27:49.091
WHERE IS HE?
[ SCOFFS ]

27:49.130 --> 27:50.119
Chloe:
HEY, COMPLIMENTS FROM TECH.

27:50.160 --> 27:52.697
THEY TRANSCRIBED ALL
OF BRIAN GOWDY'S MESSAGES.

27:52.730 --> 27:55.767
THEY'RE ALL REGARDING A SALE
OF A XJ8 ONLINE,

27:55.800 --> 27:57.336
WHICH IS WEIRD.

27:57.370 --> 27:59.702
WHY? I MEAN, HE WAS PLANNING
ON LEAVING THE COUNTRY.

27:59.740 --> 28:01.879
OF COURSE HE'S GONNA SELL
HIS CAR BEFORE HE LEAVES.

28:01.910 --> 28:03.275
YEAH, I KNOW,
BUT, UH, WHAT'S WEIRD IS,

28:03.310 --> 28:05.175
I JUST TOOK A REPORT
FROM A DIFFERENT GUY

28:05.210 --> 28:06.905
WHO'S ALSO SELLING
HIS XJ8 ONLINE.

28:06.950 --> 28:09.111
HE WAS A -- A DOCTOR,
SOME SORT OF SHRINK.

28:09.150 --> 28:10.310
UH, HE CAME
TO THE FRONT DESK,

28:10.350 --> 28:12.011
WHICH I'M CHAINED TO
'CAUSE APPARENTLY,

28:12.050 --> 28:14.109
THAT'S MY PUNISHMENT FOR GETTING
SHOT IN THE NECK, SO --

28:14.160 --> 28:15.149
CHLOE...
SORRY.

28:15.190 --> 28:18.250
IT WAS -- IT WAS --
IT WAS BLACK, RIGHT? YES.

28:18.290 --> 28:20.349
YEAH, THE SHRINK IS SELLING
THE EXACT SAME CAR ONLINE --

28:20.390 --> 28:23.097
SAME MAKE, SAME YEAR,
SAME COLOR.

28:23.130 --> 28:26.019
SO, WHAT HE SAID IS, HE TOOK
SOME GUY FOR A TEST DRIVE

28:26.070 --> 28:27.389
AND THE GUY CREEPED HIM OUT.

28:27.430 --> 28:29.830
AND I SAID, "WELL,
IT'S NOT EXACTLY ILLEGAL

28:29.870 --> 28:32.009
BECAUSE IT HAPPENS TO US LADIES
ALL THE TIME," AM I RIGHT?

28:32.040 --> 28:33.234
OKAY, SO, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT,
I WANT TO GET THIS STRAIGHT.

28:33.270 --> 28:36.933
YOU'RE SAYING THERE WERE TWO
BLACK '98 XJ8s FOR SALE ONLINE

28:36.980 --> 28:38.049
AT THE SAME TIME?

28:38.080 --> 28:39.240
CORRECT.

28:39.280 --> 28:41.145
ONE BELONGS TO BRIAN GOWDY,
ONE BELONGS TO YOUR SHRINK?

28:41.180 --> 28:42.909
YEAH. WELL, I MEAN,
HE'S NOT MY SHRINK, BUT --

28:42.950 --> 28:44.178
WE NEED TO SEE THAT REPORT.

28:44.220 --> 28:45.448
SURE.
THERE YOU GO. DONE.

28:45.490 --> 28:46.889
WE GOT TO GET THE DOCTOR
IN HERE.

28:46.920 --> 28:48.012
YEP.

28:48.060 --> 28:50.449
WE AGREED TO MEET
FOR A TEST DRIVE

28:50.490 --> 28:52.458
AT A GAS STATION ON LAKESHORE.

28:52.490 --> 28:54.390
HE, UH, GOT OUT OF HIS CAR.

28:54.430 --> 28:56.398
WHAT KIND?
GRAY.

28:56.430 --> 28:57.761
WHAT MAKE?

28:57.800 --> 29:00.121
I'M MORE
OF A PEOPLE PERSON.

29:00.170 --> 29:02.434
UM, MAYBE A SEDAN.

29:02.470 --> 29:04.301
SO, A MID-30$ MALE
WITH AN AVERAGE BUILD

29:04.340 --> 29:05.364
AND NONDESCRIPT DARK HAIR

29:05.410 --> 29:07.037
GETS IN YOUR CAR
ON THE LAKESHORE,

29:07.070 --> 29:08.799
AND YOU DIDN'T ASK
TO SEE HIS LICENSE?

29:08.840 --> 29:11.308
THAT WOULD HAVE BEEN A GOOD
IDEA, BUT, NO, I DIDN'T.

29:11.350 --> 29:13.341
HE WAS VERY ANXIOUS.

29:13.380 --> 29:18.181
WE WAS...
SILENT BUT ANGRY.

29:18.220 --> 29:19.812
DID HE THREATEN YOU
OR HARM YOU?

29:19.850 --> 29:22.250
NO, NO. HE WAS QUIET
UNTIL WE GOT TO THE WOODS,

29:22.290 --> 29:24.053
AND THEN HE STARTED IN
ON ME.

29:24.090 --> 29:26.888
HE, UH,
HE WAS INTERROGATING ME --

29:26.930 --> 29:29.421
HAD I EVER BEEN TO A MOTEL
ON KINGSTON ROAD,

29:29.460 --> 29:32.566
WAS I PLANNING A TRIP
TO COSTA RICA?

29:32.600 --> 29:35.137
UH, IT WAS LIKE HE HAD ME
CONFUSED FOR SOMEBODY ELSE.

29:35.170 --> 29:37.297
BRIAN GOWDY?
WHO?

29:37.340 --> 29:39.831
UH, TH-THAT'S OKAY.
PLEASE CONTINUE.

29:39.870 --> 29:41.201
WELL, WHEN I ASKED HIM
WHAT IT WAS ALL ABOUT,

29:41.240 --> 29:45.279
HE GOT VERY AGITATED,
TOLD ME TO GET OUT.

29:45.310 --> 29:48.108
I DIDN'T KNOW
IF HE WAS GONNA STEAL THE CAR

29:48.150 --> 29:51.347
OR -- OR KILL ME, UH...

29:51.390 --> 29:53.346
[ CHUCKLES ] I WAS TERRIFIED.

29:53.390 --> 29:55.449
AND THEN, LUCKILY,
HIS PHONE RANG

29:55.490 --> 29:58.357
AND HE GOT OUT TO ANSWER IT, SO
I JUMPED INTO THE DRIVER'S SEAT

29:58.390 --> 30:00.187
AND REVERSED THE HELL
OUT OF THERE.

30:00.230 --> 30:03.256
ANY CHANCE YOU CAN REMEMBER
WHERE HE DROVE YOU?

30:03.300 --> 30:06.463
RECONSTRUCT THE ROUTE?
OH, YEAH. YEAH, I THINK SO.

30:06.500 --> 30:08.036
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

30:08.070 --> 30:09.958
[ LOUD MUSIC PLAYING ]

30:10.000 --> 30:13.458
OKAY, [Chuckling] MAYBE I AM
GETTING A LITTLE BIT TIRED.

30:13.510 --> 30:14.499
YOU DON'T LOOK IT.

30:14.540 --> 30:16.076
I DON'T?

30:16.110 --> 30:17.509
NO.

30:17.540 --> 30:19.542
I've watched you
serve people all night.

30:19.580 --> 30:21.844
You look even better
than when you started.

30:21.880 --> 30:24.246
OKAY, THAT ONE
MIGHT WORK ON ME.

30:24.290 --> 30:27.043
MY SHIFT ENDS IN AN HOUR,
IF YOU'RE FREE.

30:27.090 --> 30:28.910
YEAH, I MIGHT BE.

30:28.960 --> 30:29.710
BOOYAH. HE'S IN.

30:29.760 --> 30:31.557
THAT GUY'S NOT GONNA
MOVE TONIGHT.

30:31.590 --> 30:32.625
LET'S PULL THE PLUG.

30:32.660 --> 30:34.389
OKAY.
I'LL TEXT DON JUAN,

30:34.430 --> 30:36.398
LET HIM KNOW
TO PULL ANGELO IN.

30:36.430 --> 30:38.022
GUESS WE'LL HAVE TO
OFFER HIM A PLEA

30:38.070 --> 30:39.094
TO COUGH UP THE GUN SELLER.

30:39.130 --> 30:40.620
DETECTIVE.
YEAH?

30:40.670 --> 30:43.901
THAT DEALER I ARRESTED
NAMED HIS SUPPLIER.

30:43.940 --> 30:45.430
UH [SIGHS]

30:45.470 --> 30:46.300
"RUSSELL THEROUX --
DIVORCED,

30:46.340 --> 30:47.602
FATHER OF TWO,
AND A MUFFLER SALESMAN."

30:47.640 --> 30:49.232
ARE Y-YOU --
YOU KIDDING ME?

30:49.280 --> 30:51.248
JAMIE SAYS
HE'S HOLDING LIKE FIVE KEYS.

30:51.280 --> 30:52.304
IS HE IN THE SYSTEM?

30:52.350 --> 30:55.239
WELL...NO, BUT --

30:55.280 --> 30:57.316
DIAZ, HO-HOW MANY TIMES
YOU WANT TO SCREW UP TONIGHT?

30:57.350 --> 30:59.341
SERIOUSLY, HUH?

30:59.390 --> 31:01.312
WITHOUT CORROBORATION,
YOU'RE GIVING ME NOTHING, OKAY?

31:01.360 --> 31:02.213
FORGET IT.

31:02.260 --> 31:04.455
ALL RIGHT, FINE,
I'LL GET YOU SOMETHING.

31:04.490 --> 31:06.253
Y-Y-- NO,
YOU'RE NOT HEARING ME.

31:06.290 --> 31:08.326
I'LL P-- I'LL PASS THIS NAME
ALONG TO THE DRUG SQUAD

31:08.360 --> 31:09.896
FOR A FOLLOW-UP.
IN THE MEANTIME,

31:09.930 --> 31:12.091
CHARGE THE DEALER
WITH SIMPLE POSSESSION.

31:12.130 --> 31:14.166
LOOK, SIR,
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,

31:14.200 --> 31:16.361
I GAVE HIM MY WORD
IF HIS INFO CHECKS OUT,

31:16.400 --> 31:18.004
HE'LL BE GIVEN CONSIDERATION.

31:18.040 --> 31:19.462
OKAY. THAT'S IT.

31:19.510 --> 31:21.205
BUT, SIR,
I PROMISED HIM IF HE --

31:23.280 --> 31:25.043
ARE WE CLEAR?
CLEAR.

31:25.080 --> 31:27.446
OKAY.

31:27.480 --> 31:29.118
BRING THE DRUGS TO EVIDENCE
AND MOVE ON.

31:35.990 --> 31:37.924
[ SIGHS ]

31:41.400 --> 31:43.391
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

31:45.300 --> 31:46.198
LET IT GO.

31:46.230 --> 31:48.164
WE COULD HAVE BUSTED
HIS SUPPLIER TONIGHT.

31:48.200 --> 31:49.030
DRUG SQUAD'S HANDLING IT.

31:49.070 --> 31:50.594
WANT TO LET THEM
TAKE ALL THE CREDIT?

31:50.640 --> 31:52.005
SINCE WHEN HAVE YOU CARED
ABOUT THAT?

31:52.040 --> 31:53.166
ALL RIGHT, YOU KNOW WHAT?
SCREW IT.

31:53.210 --> 31:54.029
I'M GONNA GO OVER THERE

31:54.080 --> 31:55.604
AND CHECK OUT THE ADDRESS
HE GAVE ME.

31:55.640 --> 31:57.608
ARE YOU INSANE?

31:57.640 --> 31:58.948
IT'S LIKE SIX BLOCKS
FROM HERE.

31:58.980 --> 32:00.106
THIS THING'S
GONE UP THE CHAIN.

32:00.150 --> 32:01.344
YOU STEP
ON AN ACTIVE INVESTIGATION,

32:01.380 --> 32:02.347
YOU'RE GONNA BLOW
YOURSELF UP.

32:02.380 --> 32:04.314
WHY DO YOU CARE SO MUCH

32:04.350 --> 32:06.341
ABOUT SETTING
SOME DEALER FREE?

32:06.390 --> 32:09.154
I DON'T CARE ABOUT HIM.

32:09.190 --> 32:10.157
OKAY,
THEN WHAT IS THIS ABOUT?

32:10.190 --> 32:11.487
'CAUSE HONESTLY,
I -- I CAN'T FIGURE IT OUT.

32:11.530 --> 32:13.179
YOU DON'T THINK THEY'RE --

32:13.230 --> 32:15.095
[ SIGHS ]

32:15.130 --> 32:17.451
YOU THINK THEY'RE NOT IN THERE
LAUGHING AT ME RIGHT NOW?

32:17.500 --> 32:21.630
IT WAS MY SCREW-UP,
AND THAT'S ON ME.

32:21.670 --> 32:22.329
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:22.370 --> 32:24.031
WHY WOULD YOU EVEN CARE,
MAN?

32:24.070 --> 32:24.866
I MEAN,
YOU'RE HAPPY, RIGHT?

32:24.910 --> 32:27.105
YOU GOT CHLOE,
AND THAT'S A GOOD THING.

32:27.140 --> 32:29.176
BUT ALL I'VE GOT
IS THIS JOB,

32:29.210 --> 32:31.974
AND LATELY I'VE BEEN
SCREWING THAT UP, TOO.

32:32.010 --> 32:32.977
ALL RIGHT, CHRIS,

32:33.010 --> 32:35.012
YOU'RE GOING THROUGH
A TOUGH TIME RIGHT NOW.

32:35.050 --> 32:37.610
I GET IT,
BUT I GOT YOUR BACK.

32:37.650 --> 32:41.154
SO, WHY DON'T YOU TAKE FIVE,
I'LL TAKE THE DRUGS TO LOCKUP,

32:41.190 --> 32:42.350
AND WE'LL GO GRAB
SOME BREAKFAST?

32:42.390 --> 32:43.459
NO.

32:43.490 --> 32:48.518
UH, WE'RE -- I GOT TO MAINTAIN
CHAIN OF CUSTODY, SO...

32:48.560 --> 32:52.291
UH, YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT, HMM?

32:52.330 --> 32:53.661
LOOK, THAN KS, I...

33:55.160 --> 33:57.151
HEY.

33:58.770 --> 33:59.759
[ BEEP ]

33:59.800 --> 34:02.098
LISTEN, UM, I'M SORRY

34:02.140 --> 34:04.108
IF I WAS A LITTLE ABRUPT
WITH YOU EARLIER.

34:04.140 --> 34:05.505
IT'S NO PROBLEM.

34:05.540 --> 34:06.666
NO, IT'S -- IT'S GOOD
THAT YOU'RE KEEN,

34:06.710 --> 34:08.109
IT'S JUST THAT
IN THIS BUSINESS,

34:08.140 --> 34:09.368
YOU KNOW,
TIMING IS EVERYTHING.

34:09.410 --> 34:11.207
DO YOU WANT ME TO GO DOWN
TO THE CELLS,

34:11.250 --> 34:12.672
SQUARE YOU
WITH THAT DRUG DEALER?

34:12.710 --> 34:14.371
I'D BE HAPPY TO
IF YOU WANT ME TO.

34:14.420 --> 34:15.717
NO.
YOU SURE?

34:15.750 --> 34:17.718
WE'RE GOOD. YEAH.

34:17.750 --> 34:19.388
YEAH?

34:19.420 --> 34:20.842
YEAH,
I TOLD HIM THE DRUG SQUAD

34:20.890 --> 34:22.517
WAS GOING TO RUN WITH IT,
SO...

34:22.560 --> 34:24.425
COOL.

34:27.460 --> 34:29.792
[ SIGHS ] OH, MY GOD,
UNBELIEVABLE.

34:29.830 --> 34:31.866
I HID THE LAST
OF THE SUGAR PACKETS HERE.

34:31.900 --> 34:35.495
GOD, I CAN'T TRUST ANYONE,
NOT EVEN COPS.

34:35.540 --> 34:36.666
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:36.700 --> 34:37.632
JUST AS WELL.

34:37.670 --> 34:41.276
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
THAT STUFF WILL KILL YOU.

34:44.880 --> 34:47.201
OKAY.

34:47.250 --> 34:48.410
SERIOUSLY,
YOU SHOULD GIVE IT UP.

34:53.550 --> 34:56.656
HEY, CURTIS, JUST, UH,
FILLING IN THE BLANKS

34:56.690 --> 34:57.679
ON TONIGHT'S BUST.

34:57.720 --> 35:00.655
IT WAS THREE GRAMS OF COKE
CHRIS CHECKED IN, RIGHT?

35:00.690 --> 35:02.226
NO.

35:02.260 --> 35:03.557
HOW MUCH WAS IT?

35:03.600 --> 35:05.864
HE HASN'T LOGGED IN
SQUAT.

35:05.900 --> 35:07.128
WHAT, ARE YOU CHECKING UP ON ME?

35:07.170 --> 35:08.535
JUST FILLING OUT
THE REPORT.

35:08.570 --> 35:09.889
IT WAS THREE GRAMS,
RIGHT?

35:09.940 --> 35:11.362
YEAH.

35:11.410 --> 35:13.628
IT'S ALL CHECKED
AND ACCOUNTED FOR.

35:15.310 --> 35:16.868
[ SIGHS ]

35:16.910 --> 35:18.207
WHERE'S THE FIELD TEST?

35:18.250 --> 35:22.175
OH, I'M SORRY.
I...I FORGOT TO DO IT.

35:22.220 --> 35:23.175
JUST GIVE IT BACK,
I'LL DO IT NOW.

35:23.220 --> 35:24.187
OH, IT'S ALL LOGGED IN ALREADY.
I'LL DO IT.

35:24.220 --> 35:26.245
DON'T KNOW WHY THEY GIVE
YOU GUYS FIELD TESTS

35:26.290 --> 35:27.279
WHEN NO ONE EVER USES THEM.

35:30.260 --> 35:32.785
[ SIGHS ]

35:32.830 --> 35:35.754
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

35:35.800 --> 35:38.894
OH, I WAS JUST IN THE LOUNGE
GETTING SQUARE WITH PECK.

35:38.930 --> 35:39.919
WHY?

35:39.970 --> 35:41.665
JUST ASKING.

35:43.840 --> 35:44.807
[ DOOR OPENS ]

35:48.510 --> 35:50.876
[ CELLPHONE DINGS ]

35:50.910 --> 35:52.571
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

35:52.610 --> 35:53.372
[ SIGHS ]

35:58.250 --> 36:00.480
YOU KNOW I HATE BREAKING
HUNDREDS FOR A COUPLE DRINKS.

36:04.960 --> 36:07.929
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL HAVE ONE MORE.

36:07.960 --> 36:10.258
I DON'T KNOW.
IT'S AFTER HOURS.

36:10.300 --> 36:11.892
YOU SERVED HIM.

36:11.930 --> 36:13.921
OKAY.

36:17.270 --> 36:18.134
BUT AFTER THIS ONE,

36:18.170 --> 36:21.708
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO DRINK
AT MY PLACE.

36:21.740 --> 36:23.628
[ SIGHS ]

36:23.680 --> 36:25.671
THAT'S A SWEET INVITATION,
BUT HERE'S THE THING --

36:25.710 --> 36:27.940
YOU'RE SMART, YOU'RE WITTY,
YOU'RE EXTREMELY ATTRACTIVE,

36:27.980 --> 36:29.447
BUT YOU ARE ALSO A CRIMINAL,

36:29.480 --> 36:31.289
WHICH IS WHY I HAVE
TO ARREST YOU

36:31.320 --> 36:32.912
FOR TRAFFICKING
ILLEGAL FIREARMS.

36:32.950 --> 36:35.418
IF THIS IS FOREPLAY,
YOU'RE DOING IT ALL WRONG.

36:35.460 --> 36:37.416
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

36:37.460 --> 36:38.449
WELL, ACTUALLY,

36:38.490 --> 36:40.822
THE INITIAL CHARGE WILL BE
SERVING ME AFTER HOURS,

36:40.860 --> 36:42.259
BUT THAT SHOULD BE ENOUGH
TO GET US A WARRANT

36:42.300 --> 36:43.824
TO SEARCH
THROUGH YOUR PHONE.

36:45.700 --> 36:47.258
[ SIGHS ]
PLEASE, GIVE IT BACK.

36:47.300 --> 36:48.767
SORRY. I'M PRETTY SURE
THOSE TEXTS YOU WERE SENDING

36:48.800 --> 36:49.664
WILL CORRESPOND WITH MESSAGES

36:49.700 --> 36:51.907
SENT TO MY FELLOW
UNDERCOVER OFFICER,

36:51.940 --> 36:53.362
AND I'M BETTING
THAT WE'LL FIND

36:53.410 --> 36:54.900
THE REST OF THE MARKED MONEY
IN YOUR BAG.

36:54.940 --> 36:56.976
YOU WOULD HAVE HAD
SO MUCH MORE FUN

36:57.010 --> 36:58.841
IF YOU JUST CAME HOME
WITH ME.

36:58.880 --> 37:00.768
BUT I WOULD HAVE REGRETTED IT
IN THE MORNING.

37:08.390 --> 37:10.984
[ SIREN WAILING ]

37:11.020 --> 37:13.284
CHRIS.

37:13.330 --> 37:14.627
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

37:14.660 --> 37:15.558
YEAH, I'M FINE.

37:15.600 --> 37:18.524
JUST RIGHT NOW ALL I NEED
IS SOME SLEEP.

37:18.570 --> 37:20.925
THAT BUST OF YOURS,
THE DRUG DEALER FROM THE ALLEY,

37:20.970 --> 37:22.289
WE'RE KICKING HIM LOOSE.

37:22.340 --> 37:23.591
WHOA,
WHAT'S GOING ON?

37:23.640 --> 37:25.562
CURTIS TESTED THE COKE.
IT AIN'T.

37:25.610 --> 37:26.804
IT'S PURE BAKING SODA.

37:26.840 --> 37:28.933
ARE YOU SERIOUS?
YEAH.

37:28.980 --> 37:30.936
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
EVEN IF HE'S A SCAMMER,

37:30.980 --> 37:32.868
WE CAN STILL
CHARGE HIM WITH DEALING.

37:32.910 --> 37:34.810
DID HE ACTUALLY SAY
IT WAS COKE?

37:34.850 --> 37:36.909
NO. HE WAS JUST
FLASHING THE BAGGIES,

37:36.950 --> 37:38.747
LIKE, "LOOK WHAT I GOT."
HE...

37:38.790 --> 37:39.449
Steve: YEAH?

37:39.490 --> 37:40.582
[ SIGHS ]
SEE, WE GOT NOTHING.

37:40.620 --> 37:41.951
THE GUY WAS SELLING ALL NIGHT.
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.

37:41.990 --> 37:43.150
Steve: NO, IT DOESN'T,

37:43.190 --> 37:45.829
AND THIS WHOLE THING HAS BEEN
IN SHAMBLES FROM THE GET-GO.

37:45.860 --> 37:48.351
I'M DONE WITH IT,
KICKING HIM LOOSE.

37:48.400 --> 37:49.651
SEE YOU LATER.

37:57.470 --> 37:58.334
ALIEN.

37:58.370 --> 38:00.338
I NEVER PROPERLY
THANKED YOU FOR THIS.

38:00.370 --> 38:02.008
UH, LOOK,
I KNOW I'VE BEEN SLACKING.

38:02.040 --> 38:04.372
HERE'S THE JAMESON REPORT.
I FINALLY FINISHED IT.

38:04.410 --> 38:05.308
OKAY.
COME AND SIT DOWN.

38:05.350 --> 38:06.339
WE'RE GONNA CHAT
FOR A BIT.

38:16.720 --> 38:19.951
THE LAST LITTLE WHILE,
IT'S -- THAT'S NOT LIKE YOU.

38:23.760 --> 38:24.966
IT'S HOLLY?

38:25.000 --> 38:27.696
YOU HEARD.
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:27.730 --> 38:29.664
THAT'S GREAT.

38:29.700 --> 38:32.100
I'M R-- I'M SORRY THAT
THAT DIDN'T WORK OUT.

38:32.140 --> 38:34.335
YEAH, WHO KNOWS?
I DON'T KNOW.

38:34.380 --> 38:36.837
MAYBE IT WILL.
I GUESS THAT'S PART OF IT.

38:36.880 --> 38:38.438
OKAY,
WHAT'S THE OTHER PART?

38:38.480 --> 38:41.347
THIS.
IT'S THIS --

38:41.380 --> 38:44.588
SOME WOMAN WHO GOT SHOT
IN THE LAUNDRY ROOM.

38:44.620 --> 38:47.111
IT'S THE LITTLE GIRL?

38:47.150 --> 38:50.551
HER NAME IS SOPHIE,
AND SHE'S 8 YEARS OLD.

38:50.590 --> 38:51.579
MM.

38:51.630 --> 38:54.428
[Voice breaking ] AND WHEN
SHE GETS TO KNOW YOU,

38:54.460 --> 38:56.496
SHE JUST HAS
THE MOST INCREDIBLE SMILE.

38:56.530 --> 38:57.258
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:57.300 --> 38:59.621
SHE'S JUST SO OPEN
TO THE WORLD,

38:59.670 --> 39:01.638
AND THEN, WELL,
WHAT DOES THE WORLD DO?

39:01.670 --> 39:03.365
IT GOES IN
AND DOES THIS TO HER,

39:03.400 --> 39:06.836
AND NOW SHE DOESN'T HAVE
A FAMILY AND SHE'S ALL ALONE.

39:06.870 --> 39:09.100
AND I DON'T REALLY KNOW
WHAT'S, UM...

39:09.140 --> 39:12.439
I DON'T KNOW WHY I CAN'T GET
THIS ONE OUT OF MY HEAD,

39:12.480 --> 39:15.369
AND I KNOW THAT WE'VE BEEN
THROUGH WORSE CASES.

39:15.420 --> 39:18.116
I MEAN, WE ALL HAVE.

39:18.150 --> 39:21.779
I DON'T REALLY KNOW
WHAT IT IS ABOUT THIS ONE.

39:21.820 --> 39:24.880
IT GOT YOU.

39:24.930 --> 39:27.558
THAT'S ALL.
IT IS THE WORST FOR YOU.

39:27.590 --> 39:31.822
YEAH? HUH?
BREAKS THE SKIN.

39:31.870 --> 39:34.168
AND NOW, I'M SORRY,

39:34.200 --> 39:38.603
BUT, UH, EVERYTHING IS GONNA
HURT A LITTLE BIT MORE.

39:38.640 --> 39:39.664
[ SIGHS ]

39:39.710 --> 39:42.531
AND THAT'S OKAY.
THAT'S HOW IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE.

39:42.580 --> 39:47.449
THAT'S...GOOD, EXCEPT FOR
THE HURTING PART. THAT BITES.

39:47.480 --> 39:51.109
BUT IT'S -- IT'S GOOD.

39:51.150 --> 39:54.654
IF YOU EVER NEED ANYTHING,
ANYTHING AT ALL...

39:54.690 --> 39:57.409
LIKE...WEAPONS?

39:57.460 --> 39:58.552
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:58.590 --> 39:59.989
YEAH. [ CHUCKLES ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:00.030 --> 40:02.828
OR SHOES, RIGHT?
YOU WANT TO SHOP?

40:02.860 --> 40:06.819
LISTEN, YOU GOT IT, OKAY?
FOR REAL.

40:06.870 --> 40:08.189
YOU KNOW [STUTTERS]

40:08.230 --> 40:11.097
I'M STILL YOUR FRIEND,
GAIL.

40:15.010 --> 40:16.477
OKAY.
[ PATS BACK ]

40:16.510 --> 40:19.741
HEY, IT'S OKAY, KIDDO.

40:19.780 --> 40:20.906
IT'S OKAY.

40:24.490 --> 40:26.117
LOOK, MAN,
I JUST WANT TO APOLOGIZE

40:26.150 --> 40:28.015
FOR WHAT HAPPENED
IN THERE, YOU KNOW?

40:28.050 --> 40:30.052
BUT AT LEAST YOU'RE GETTING OUT
OF HERE WITHOUT A CHARGE.

40:30.090 --> 40:32.479
NO, NO.

40:32.530 --> 40:34.919
I DID YOU THE FAVOR,
OKAY?

40:34.960 --> 40:37.099
YOU OWE ME,
SO DON'T THINK FOR A SECOND

40:37.130 --> 40:38.893
I WON'T COME BACK
TO COLLECT.

40:38.930 --> 40:41.933
I'LL SEE YOU LATER,
MIDTOWN.

40:41.970 --> 40:45.007
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:45.040 --> 40:46.530
[ SIREN WAILS ]

40:55.920 --> 40:57.615
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

41:04.160 --> 41:07.152
I'M BEGINNING TO HAVE
SECOND THOUGHTS ABOUT THIS.

41:07.190 --> 41:08.282
IT LOOKS DIFFERENT.

41:08.330 --> 41:11.822
I MEAN, MAYBE -- MAYBE
IT'S A DIFFERENT PARKING LOT.

41:11.870 --> 41:13.861
IT'S -- IT'S AROUND HERE
SOMEWHERE.

41:13.900 --> 41:16.130
I REMEMBER THERE WAS A VIEW
LIKE THIS,

41:16.170 --> 41:20.732
BUT, UH...I DON'T KNOW.

41:20.770 --> 41:23.136
SAM.

41:24.780 --> 41:25.906
UH, SIR, WOULD YOU MIND

41:25.950 --> 41:28.009
WAITING IN THE CAR
FOR A MINUTE, PLEASE?

41:46.770 --> 41:47.862
OH...

41:47.900 --> 41:50.130
[ SIGHS ]

41:50.170 --> 41:52.604
WASN'T SUPPOSED
TO END THIS WAY.

41:52.640 --> 41:55.973
WELL, IT'S NOT OVER.
